This paper deals with the optimization of network configuration for functional and security requirements, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of software-defined networks, which is a subfield of computer networks and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses risk requirements, which is related to security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a layered framework for optimization, which involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the validation of the approach through experiments, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
